From 5ce6a6e6c42da704bb5536f166c1bc1110dbc98a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Saravanakumar Duraisamy <saradura@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 21 May 2025 23:13:22 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PLATFORM:wifi:ath12k: ath_debug module support for
 ath12k driver

ath_debug module is a standalone module which will provide
the debugging functionaity to ath12k. It will provide the
implementation of debug feature which are non-upstreamable
and provide interface to access the ath12k exsisting debugging
feature.

Interfaces:
- athdbg_if_register - Ath12k driver can register with debug driver
- athdbg_if_unregister - Resource related to debug usecase can be freed
- athdbg_if_get_service - to perform any action that need to be done in
                          the ath12k driver flow
- dbg_to_ath_ops - Callback can trigger from ath_debug to ath12k

Supports:
- Debug mask enablement
- Minidump enablement

Usage:
echo <mask> > /sys/kernel/debug/ath12k/<device>/ath_debug/dbgmask

Ex:
echo wmi > /sys/kernel/debug/ath12k/pci-0003:01:00.0/ath_debug/dbgmask
echo "wmi:htc:mac" > /sys/kernel/debug/ath12k/pci-0003:01:00.0/ath_debug/dbgmask

Signed-off-by: Saravanakumar Duraisamy <saradura@qti.qualcomm.com>
